Jaguar Cars Inc, a subsidiary of JaguarPLC, said it introduced its new 1988 XJ6 luxury sedan toreplace its Series III XJ6 sedan.    The 40,500-dlr car will be available in showrooms startingMay four, the company said.    Many parts of the XJ6 and the 44,500 dlr Vanden Plas havebeen changed, adding high-tech features. The car has sevenmicro-processors that control its major electrical functions.The in-car computer offers a wide array of trip information.    The Vanden Plas offers more features than the basic XJ6.    Jaguar said it has a "substantial waiting list" for thecars in Europe, where it was introduced last October. Reuter&#3;